        "content": "<p>I've seen a bunch of sources (the nLab, Maclane-Moerdijk, for example) formulate the axioms for a Lawvere-Tierney topology in terms of an arrow <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>j</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ω</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ω</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">j : \\Omega \\to \\Omega</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.854em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05724em;\">j</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ω</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ω</span></span></span></span> and mention that the axioms can also be specified in terms of properties of the corresponding subobject <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>J</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">J</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span></span></span></span>, but none of them that I've looked at actually seems to include or reference such a presentation.  Is there a source that has this?</p>",
        "id": 410732831,
        "sender_full_name": "James Deikun",
        "timestamp": 1704123339
    },
